args: Aaah... Lanterns and music really make\nya feel like you're at a festival.
I just came to bring you some food from\nthe stalls. You've been busy monitoring\neverything and I know you haven't eaten.
Well, thanks a million! Oh hey,\nis this from the fishmonger's stall?
Everyone seems to agree with you—\nthey've been doing a lot of business.
Glad to hear it! I was only able to\nstop by for a brief ＂hi,＂ so I didn't\nknow how things were going.
The food is incredible, and that art piece\nat the florist was simply stunning.
Yeah, the owner was pretty proud of that.
I'm glad folks got to see it.
This festival is making everyone happy.
I've never seen so many smiling faces.
Yeah, they're somethin' all right.\nSo which part didja like best?
That's a good eye ya got, Princey.
The float was what caught my eye\nat MY first festival, too.

Yeah. It was love at first sight.
The folks liftin' it... Everyone watchin'...
They were all so full of life, and it was
like they were united as one!
Somethin' about a float just reaches out\nand grabs your heart, ya know?
It really was the star of the festival.
You really do love floats, don't you?
Ya better believe it! Hell, leadin' the float\nin the parade is my favorite part'a the job.
It's like I'm spreadin' cheer\neverywhere I go.
Ya can't beat that with a stick.
I'm glad we were able to bring it out,\ndespite the difficulties.
I guess when you think about it,\nI'm kind of like a float myself.
Well, both countries and royalty are\n＂carried＂ by the general population.
I mean, sure, we all shoulder our\ncountries like a float to some extent,\nbut you ain't exactly bein' carried.

Hell no! You're out in the front lines
helpin' folks or whatever. In truth,
you're more like the guy what CARRIES
the float than somebody ridin' on it.
Huh. I didn't think of it like that.
Still, I think I have a long way to go.
I'd give anything to have your confidence.
Me? I doubt myself all the damn time!
'Course I do—I just can't SAY nothin'\nabout it once the festival gets goin'.
Instead, I just charge ahead and hope\nit all comes out clean in the wash.
Once everything's over, then I can go\nback, figure out what I did wrong,\nand make it better the next time.
I love what I do, so I wanna keep gettin'\nbetter at it. What about you?
I suppose I'm the same way.
I love this country and its people,\nso as flawed as I am, I'm going to\ncharge in and help however I can.
Hey, that gives me an idea!
Let's both swear to become\nthe best leaders we can be!
C'mon! Nothin' motivates a person like\nhavin' someone else with the same goal!
So let's both swear to become\nthe best leaders we can.
One day, I WILL become a man\nfit to lead this country.
And I'll become somebody whose float\ncan liven up ANY town!
Right then! Three cheers to the future!
